  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support 50 blind Girls to participate in education</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Uganda only 9% of school age going children with disability is estimated to have enrolled in primary school compared to the national average of 92%. Of the 9% only 6% are able to transition to secondary school.  In communities where people face challenges to provide for their own basic needs, education for a girl with disability is not an option; Girls with Disability often have no chance in accessing an education.The attitude towards the education of girls with disability is negative.</narrative>
  </description>
